1
00:00:01,668 --> 00:00:03,603
( Whooshing )

2
00:00:07,741 --> 00:00:09,643
Narrator:
The recently revived king,

3
00:00:09,710 --> 00:00:13,347
now calling himself meruem,
headed back to the palace

4
00:00:13,413 --> 00:00:17,517
to recover his memories
with pouf and youpi in tow.

5
00:00:21,221 --> 00:00:23,156
♪

6
00:00:25,659 --> 00:00:27,561
Palm: I can see
pouf’s main body.

7
00:00:27,628 --> 00:00:28,729
It’s with the king.

8
00:00:28,795 --> 00:00:30,196
( Knuckle gasps )

9
00:00:30,264 --> 00:00:32,299
Palm: They’re heading
toward the palace

10
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:33,667
at an incredible speed.

11
00:00:33,734 --> 00:00:34,802
( Knuckle growls )

12
00:00:37,337 --> 00:00:39,339
That can only mean one thing.

13
00:00:39,406 --> 00:00:41,074
The chairman lost.

14
00:00:41,141 --> 00:00:45,312
If he couldn’t do it,
what can the rest of us do?

15
00:00:47,147 --> 00:00:48,081
♪

16
00:00:48,148 --> 00:00:50,083
( Singing in Japanese )

17
00:01:31,525 --> 00:01:33,460
♪

18
00:01:45,506 --> 00:01:48,576
Komugi: I wish someone
would tell me what’s happening.

19
00:01:48,642 --> 00:01:51,445
Where did the dear leader go?

20
00:01:57,150 --> 00:01:59,352
Meruem: It won’t
stop following us.

21
00:01:59,419 --> 00:02:01,321
The sight of it annoys me.

22
00:02:01,388 --> 00:02:03,624
Menthuthuyoupi:
It’s the enemy’s power, sire.

23
00:02:03,690 --> 00:02:06,793
I think the only way
that we can get it to disappear

24
00:02:06,860 --> 00:02:09,029
is to hurt the enemy himself.

25
00:02:09,096 --> 00:02:12,333
Meruem: Ah. Interesting.

26
00:02:12,399 --> 00:02:14,434
Then let’s find out.

27
00:02:15,602 --> 00:02:17,137
( Shaiapouf gasps )

28
00:02:17,204 --> 00:02:19,640
Menthuthuyoupi: Incredible.

29
00:02:19,706 --> 00:02:21,608
Is that really my--

30
00:02:35,489 --> 00:02:36,757
( Gasps )

31
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:40,327
( Shaiapouf gasps )

32
00:02:50,704 --> 00:02:52,105
Meruem: I see.

33
00:02:52,172 --> 00:02:54,374
Menthuthuyoupi: I was wrong.

34
00:02:54,441 --> 00:02:57,477
My power was never meant
for me to use.

35
00:02:57,544 --> 00:03:00,313
It was meant to be used
by the king himself.

36
00:03:01,548 --> 00:03:02,716
- Meruem: Youpi.
- Menthuthuyoupi: Huh?

37
00:03:04,218 --> 00:03:06,554
Meruem: This doesn’t
make any sense.

38
00:03:06,620 --> 00:03:09,156
- Menthuthuyoupi: Eh?
- ( Shaiapouf gasps )

39
00:03:09,223 --> 00:03:12,259
Meruem: You were already
aware that this power

40
00:03:12,326 --> 00:03:14,728
was the result
of an enemy attack,

41
00:03:14,795 --> 00:03:18,799
and for you to know that,
you either saw it used,

42
00:03:18,866 --> 00:03:22,036
or it was used
on you personally.

43
00:03:23,337 --> 00:03:25,072
So which is it?

44
00:03:25,138 --> 00:03:27,440
♪

45
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:34,482
Menthuthuyoupi: I saw him
and was hit by an attack.

46
00:03:34,548 --> 00:03:37,084
( Shaiapouf gasps )

47
00:03:37,150 --> 00:03:39,285
Meruem: It’s not on you now.

48
00:03:39,353 --> 00:03:42,756
That thing is
not following you anymore,

49
00:03:42,823 --> 00:03:45,793
so why does the enemy
still draw breath?

50
00:03:45,859 --> 00:03:48,395
( Menthuthuyoupi stammers )

51
00:03:48,462 --> 00:03:50,230
Meruem: I want you to tell me

52
00:03:50,297 --> 00:03:53,066
how you deactivated
the enemy’s ability.

53
00:03:54,201 --> 00:03:55,402
Well?

54
00:03:55,469 --> 00:03:56,470
( Menthuthuyoupi sighs )

55
00:03:59,806 --> 00:04:03,043
Okay, the truth is
we made an agreement.

56
00:04:03,110 --> 00:04:06,647
In exchange for releasing me
from his power,

57
00:04:06,713 --> 00:04:08,748
I agreed to spare his comrade.

58
00:04:11,251 --> 00:04:13,286
Meruem: Then,
after he released you,

59
00:04:13,353 --> 00:04:16,022
you had the opportunity
to finish his comrade

60
00:04:16,089 --> 00:04:19,559
and him as well.
Why didn’t you do so?

61
00:04:19,626 --> 00:04:23,330
Menthuthuyoupi:
Honestly, I have no idea.

62
00:04:26,533 --> 00:04:28,135
I suppose I felt

63
00:04:28,202 --> 00:04:32,573
like I couldn’t lose
to the enemy in any way.

64
00:04:32,639 --> 00:04:34,508
I thought breaking a promise,

65
00:04:34,575 --> 00:04:37,778
even a promise I made
to one of my enemies,

66
00:04:37,845 --> 00:04:40,081
would be like
conceding defeat.

67
00:04:40,147 --> 00:04:41,448
Shaiapouf: Ridiculous!

68
00:04:41,515 --> 00:04:43,650
You deliberately passed up
the perfect opportunity

69
00:04:43,717 --> 00:04:46,320
to remove every last threat
to the king,

70
00:04:46,386 --> 00:04:49,055
all because
of some ambiguous feeling?

71
00:04:50,457 --> 00:04:52,426
Menthuthuyoupi:
Punish me however you want.

72
00:04:52,492 --> 00:04:54,060
I deserve it.

73
00:04:55,295 --> 00:04:58,064
There is no excuse
for what I did.

74
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:06,339
Meruem: I only ordered
that you not lie to me.

75
00:05:06,406 --> 00:05:07,674
You told the truth.

76
00:05:07,741 --> 00:05:10,143
I won’t punish you
for your honesty.

77
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:12,345
You did just as I asked of you.

78
00:05:12,412 --> 00:05:13,747
Menthuthuyoupi: Ah?

79
00:05:13,814 --> 00:05:15,349
( Shaiapouf gasps )

80
00:05:15,415 --> 00:05:16,750
Meruem: Now, pouf.

81
00:05:16,817 --> 00:05:18,152
Shaiapouf: Sire.

82
00:05:18,218 --> 00:05:20,754
- Meruem: Youpi.
- Menthuthuyoupi: Sire!

83
00:05:20,821 --> 00:05:24,358
Meruem: Our relationships
have become quite complex.

84
00:05:24,424 --> 00:05:27,360
( Both gasp )

85
00:05:27,427 --> 00:05:30,196
Meruem: It seems
that our bodies and souls

86
00:05:30,264 --> 00:05:33,601
have become intertwined,
and, as a result of this fact,

87
00:05:33,667 --> 00:05:36,336
there can be no more secrets
between us.

88
00:05:39,773 --> 00:05:41,275
Menthuthuyoupi: Sire!

89
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:43,443
Shaiapouf: Sire.

90
00:05:44,545 --> 00:05:45,746
Meruem: Let’s go.

91
00:05:45,812 --> 00:05:47,447
Both: Right.

92
00:05:51,885 --> 00:05:54,554
Shaiapouf: Sire,
have you somehow realized

93
00:05:54,621 --> 00:05:56,556
what it is I plan to do?

94
00:05:56,623 --> 00:05:59,292
Was that meant as some sort
of final warning?

95
00:05:59,359 --> 00:06:03,096
Do you sense how my guilt
tears away at me?

96
00:06:04,832 --> 00:06:09,503
Nevertheless, even if it means
I am executed for my crime...

97
00:06:11,572 --> 00:06:13,507
I do this for the king!

98
00:06:14,575 --> 00:06:16,310
( Segments muttering )

99
00:06:16,376 --> 00:06:18,011
- Find her.
- Find her quickly.

100
00:06:18,078 --> 00:06:20,113
- Hurry up. Find her.
- Hurry up, and find her.

101
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:22,616
Shaiapouf: For the sake
of our species...

102
00:06:22,683 --> 00:06:24,051
Segment: Find her.

103
00:06:24,117 --> 00:06:25,085
- Find her quickly.
- Find her.

104
00:06:26,420 --> 00:06:28,522
Shaiapouf: She is not necessary.

105
00:06:28,589 --> 00:06:29,690
Segment: Where is she?

106
00:06:29,756 --> 00:06:31,625
Shaiapouf:
I do this for the king.

107
00:06:31,692 --> 00:06:33,727
- Segment: There? No.
- Is she over there?

108
00:06:33,794 --> 00:06:35,129
( Chatter continues )

109
00:06:35,195 --> 00:06:36,530
Knuckle: Hey there.

110
00:06:36,597 --> 00:06:38,365
( Segments gasp )

111
00:06:38,432 --> 00:06:40,334
Knuckle: I’ve got you pegged.

112
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:43,536
You can’t hurt me
when you’re split up, can you?

113
00:06:43,604 --> 00:06:45,206
♪

114
00:06:46,273 --> 00:06:47,541
( Stammers )

115
00:06:47,608 --> 00:06:50,478
Where are you going?!
I’m talking to you!

116
00:06:50,544 --> 00:06:53,547
You can’t remove a.P.R.
’til you beat me!

117
00:06:53,614 --> 00:06:57,218
Shaiapouf: Youpi, the enemy
has just appeared before me.

118
00:06:58,352 --> 00:06:59,553
He attached this thing,

119
00:06:59,620 --> 00:07:01,288
but can he teleport, too?

120
00:07:01,355 --> 00:07:03,057
Menthuthuyoupi:
No, that’s somebody else.

121
00:07:03,123 --> 00:07:04,491
There’s one who can make himself

122
00:07:04,558 --> 00:07:06,393
and everyone
around him invisible.

123
00:07:06,460 --> 00:07:08,696
He looks just like a chameleon.

124
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:12,099
I don’t know his name,
but he’s a squadron leader,

125
00:07:12,166 --> 00:07:14,101
which means he’s a traitor.

126
00:07:14,168 --> 00:07:16,337
Shaiapouf: So you
spared a traitor?

127
00:07:16,403 --> 00:07:19,539
Those humans, I might have been
able to forgive, but never this.

128
00:07:19,606 --> 00:07:20,540
( Menthuthuyoupi gasps )

129
00:07:20,607 --> 00:07:23,210
Then punish me if you have to,

130
00:07:23,277 --> 00:07:27,014
but, sire, I beg you to please
wait until we’ve defeated them.

131
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:30,050
Meruem: I don’t care.
It’s pointless.

132
00:07:30,117 --> 00:07:34,622
On the contrary, this is a trial
we chimera ants must overcome

133
00:07:34,688 --> 00:07:37,424
if we are to truly continue
our evolution.

134
00:07:37,491 --> 00:07:40,227
( Both gasp )

135
00:07:40,294 --> 00:07:45,032
Meruem: Youpi,
your own emotional instability,

136
00:07:45,098 --> 00:07:47,734
as well
as the traitor’s betrayal,

137
00:07:47,801 --> 00:07:51,104
we must accept them
and move forward.

138
00:07:52,206 --> 00:07:53,607
Humans are a steppingstone

139
00:07:53,674 --> 00:07:56,810
meant to help us attain
the next level of evolution,

140
00:07:56,877 --> 00:07:58,712
the perfect sacrifice.

141
00:08:01,215 --> 00:08:04,485
The remnants of human ego
within us are variables,

142
00:08:04,551 --> 00:08:06,486
as long as we consider them

143
00:08:06,553 --> 00:08:09,356
but a transitional phase
to our final form.

144
00:08:12,626 --> 00:08:15,362
Narrator: The king’s opinion
had completely reversed

145
00:08:15,429 --> 00:08:17,131
following the explosion.

146
00:08:17,197 --> 00:08:19,366
Was this a result of the blast?

147
00:08:21,168 --> 00:08:24,405
No. They were both
part of the king.

148
00:08:24,471 --> 00:08:27,374
Shaiapouf: If the enemy
can become invisible,

149
00:08:27,441 --> 00:08:30,311
I can find him
by making contact.

150
00:08:30,377 --> 00:08:33,413
I need to split myself
into the smallest segments

151
00:08:33,480 --> 00:08:38,385
that can still see
and then expand the search.

152
00:08:43,090 --> 00:08:44,458
Knuckle: Bastard.

153
00:08:44,525 --> 00:08:47,628
I’m not his target.
That much is obvious.

154
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:50,297
He turned back just like that.

155
00:08:50,364 --> 00:08:51,599
Who is he after?

156
00:08:54,501 --> 00:08:57,237
Is he looking for meleoron,
the traitor?

157
00:08:57,304 --> 00:08:59,640
Because that would be bad.

158
00:08:59,706 --> 00:09:02,209
We have to defeat the king,

159
00:09:02,276 --> 00:09:06,380
but I don’t see how we can
without meleoron’s ability.

160
00:09:06,446 --> 00:09:10,550
I’ve got to protect meleoron,
no matter the cost.

161
00:09:14,655 --> 00:09:17,158
Palm: Pouf divided
his segments to the point

162
00:09:17,224 --> 00:09:19,727
that they’re
too small for me to see.

163
00:09:19,793 --> 00:09:21,995
Unlike his main body,

164
00:09:22,062 --> 00:09:25,265
his segments have to be
at full size for me to see them.

165
00:09:28,769 --> 00:09:31,105
Shaiapouf:
The man with the pompadour

166
00:09:31,171 --> 00:09:33,206
was obviously just a decoy.

167
00:09:33,273 --> 00:09:36,643
They must know that we’ve
made sense of it by now

168
00:09:36,710 --> 00:09:39,313
and we know
the chameleon is a traitor.

169
00:09:39,379 --> 00:09:43,350
In other words, they believe
that’s why i’ve returned,

170
00:09:43,417 --> 00:09:45,586
to dispose
of the double-crosser.

171
00:09:46,854 --> 00:09:48,389
Assuming that the chameleon

172
00:09:48,455 --> 00:09:51,425
is concealing himself
and the others as they flee

173
00:09:51,491 --> 00:09:53,193
and assuming
that the woman is among them,

174
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:55,229
I can’t get too close.

175
00:09:55,295 --> 00:09:57,631
If I do, they will
protect the chameleon

176
00:09:57,698 --> 00:10:00,100
and abandon her.
I’m certain of it.

177
00:10:01,401 --> 00:10:03,570
They believe
the chameleon is my target.

178
00:10:03,637 --> 00:10:06,240
If they only knew
how wrong they are.

179
00:10:06,306 --> 00:10:09,743
They’d never imagine that I
would return to kill the woman

180
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:13,347
pitou was trying
so desperately to heal.

181
00:10:13,413 --> 00:10:16,049
If they’re under the impression
that i’ve come back

182
00:10:16,116 --> 00:10:19,653
in order to rescue the woman,
well, that’s even better.

183
00:10:19,720 --> 00:10:23,657
And if i’m lucky, they may even
offer to hand her over to me,

184
00:10:23,724 --> 00:10:25,526
with conditions, of course.

185
00:10:28,629 --> 00:10:30,598
♪

186
00:10:30,664 --> 00:10:34,368
Knuckle: That little monster’s
after meleoron. He must be.

187
00:10:34,434 --> 00:10:36,102
It would make perfect sense,

188
00:10:36,170 --> 00:10:39,306
because, to them, he’s nothing
more than a traitor.

189
00:10:39,373 --> 00:10:40,774
Killua: Hold on.

190
00:10:42,876 --> 00:10:45,379
We need to be sure about it.

191
00:10:51,218 --> 00:10:52,853
( Panel buzzes )

192
00:10:54,788 --> 00:10:56,323
( Segments gasp )

193
00:10:56,390 --> 00:10:58,325
♪

194
00:11:02,529 --> 00:11:04,331
( Breeze blowing )

195
00:11:05,599 --> 00:11:08,102
Shaiapouf: The door
leading underground?

196
00:11:09,203 --> 00:11:10,571
So that’s it.

197
00:11:10,637 --> 00:11:13,373
They’ve realized I know
they can become invisible,

198
00:11:13,440 --> 00:11:16,109
and they’ve decided
to give me two options.

199
00:11:16,176 --> 00:11:18,812
Either the chameleon ran inside,

200
00:11:18,879 --> 00:11:21,415
or he fled
somewhere else entirely.

201
00:11:21,481 --> 00:11:24,651
That’s their plan.
They intend to weaken me

202
00:11:24,718 --> 00:11:28,088
by splitting up my segments
even further.

203
00:11:28,155 --> 00:11:30,124
- ( Segments chattering )
- No. Over there.

204
00:11:30,190 --> 00:11:31,291
- Over there.
- Over there.

205
00:11:31,358 --> 00:11:32,459
- There.
- Over there.

206
00:11:32,526 --> 00:11:33,527
- Over there.
- Over there.

207
00:11:33,594 --> 00:11:35,329
( Shaiapouf gasps )

208
00:11:35,395 --> 00:11:37,330
♪

209
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:40,634
What?

210
00:11:44,805 --> 00:11:45,439
♪

211
00:11:46,607 --> 00:11:47,675
♪

212
00:11:55,449 --> 00:11:57,351
Shaiapouf:
They’re giving me a choice.

213
00:11:57,417 --> 00:12:00,587
I can either pursue
the traitor or the girl.

214
00:12:00,654 --> 00:12:02,356
( Groans )

215
00:12:02,422 --> 00:12:06,393
So they want to determine
what my target is. Is that it?

216
00:12:07,494 --> 00:12:09,196
What should I do?

217
00:12:09,263 --> 00:12:12,433
Do I split up my segments
to hide my objective,

218
00:12:12,499 --> 00:12:15,202
or do I send the majority
of them after the chameleon

219
00:12:15,269 --> 00:12:17,371
in order to try
and fool the enemy?

220
00:12:18,505 --> 00:12:20,707
Even if the shutters are closed,

221
00:12:20,774 --> 00:12:24,144
I can slip through it if
my segments are particle-sized.

222
00:12:24,211 --> 00:12:27,014
No. There’s no time.

223
00:12:32,119 --> 00:12:33,654
I’ve made my decision.

224
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,655
I’ll go after the girl!

225
00:12:35,722 --> 00:12:38,458
Killua: So she’s his target?

226
00:12:38,525 --> 00:12:40,494
Shaiapouf: I only
have to kill the woman

227
00:12:40,561 --> 00:12:43,464
and hide her body from the king
for a short time.

228
00:12:43,530 --> 00:12:45,465
My segment can manage that.

229
00:12:45,532 --> 00:12:47,267
I only need a minute!

230
00:12:47,334 --> 00:12:48,635
♪

231
00:12:56,343 --> 00:12:58,245
- ( Electricity crackles )
- ( Shaiapouf gasps )

232
00:13:00,147 --> 00:13:01,615
I see.

233
00:13:01,682 --> 00:13:06,187
This boy,
he’s unbelievably fast.

234
00:13:08,021 --> 00:13:09,456
Killua: So she’s
your target, huh?

235
00:13:09,523 --> 00:13:12,226
Well, i’m up for a game of tag,

236
00:13:12,292 --> 00:13:15,629
and I can play all night long.

237
00:13:15,696 --> 00:13:16,730
( Shaiapouf gasps )

238
00:13:16,797 --> 00:13:19,433
Judging by
how quickly he reacted,

239
00:13:19,500 --> 00:13:22,303
it would be nearly impossible
for me to catch him,

240
00:13:22,369 --> 00:13:24,738
even at full strength.

241
00:13:24,805 --> 00:13:27,408
If I don’t hurry,
the king will arrive.

242
00:13:27,474 --> 00:13:29,142
What do I do?

243
00:13:29,209 --> 00:13:31,745
Narrator: Pressured
by the crisis he faced,

244
00:13:31,812 --> 00:13:34,648
pouf came up with an evil plan.

245
00:13:34,715 --> 00:13:35,749
Shaiapouf: That’s it.

246
00:13:35,816 --> 00:13:39,186
I know the perfect magic trick.

247
00:13:40,254 --> 00:13:41,355
( Killua gasps )

248
00:13:41,421 --> 00:13:43,757
He split himself into pieces?

249
00:13:43,824 --> 00:13:46,327
But he won’t be big enough
to take her away.

250
00:13:47,628 --> 00:13:49,096
What’s his plan?

251
00:13:49,163 --> 00:13:51,132
Is he gonna attack me first?

252
00:13:52,299 --> 00:13:53,634
That’s gonna backfire.

253
00:13:55,202 --> 00:13:57,171
You’ve reduced
your speed and power,

254
00:13:57,237 --> 00:13:59,773
which means I don’t need
to use godspeed anymore.

255
00:13:59,840 --> 00:14:03,143
Shaiapouf: Don’t you see
that resistance is futile?

256
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:05,212
All of your
so carefully laid plans

257
00:14:05,279 --> 00:14:06,413
have already been foiled.

258
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,614
( Killua gasps )

259
00:14:07,681 --> 00:14:09,283
Shaiapouf: Knowing that,

260
00:14:09,349 --> 00:14:11,585
what’s the point in adding
to your transgressions?

261
00:14:11,652 --> 00:14:14,155
If fear of punishment
is driving you to flee,

262
00:14:14,221 --> 00:14:15,222
you needn’t worry.

263
00:14:15,289 --> 00:14:17,591
The king will forgive you.

264
00:14:18,692 --> 00:14:21,428
He is quite a benevolent ruler.

265
00:14:21,495 --> 00:14:23,130
Killua: Don’t make me laugh!

266
00:14:23,197 --> 00:14:25,199
You really think
i’m gonna believe that?!

267
00:14:25,265 --> 00:14:27,267
You’ll probably
just tie me to a tree

268
00:14:27,334 --> 00:14:29,002
and turn me into a soldier.

269
00:14:30,137 --> 00:14:31,438
Komugi: The king?

270
00:14:31,505 --> 00:14:33,440
( Shaiapouf chuckles )

271
00:14:33,507 --> 00:14:36,043
♪

272
00:14:36,109 --> 00:14:38,211
Yes, that’s right.
Keep running,

273
00:14:38,278 --> 00:14:41,214
and don’t stop until you’re
far from the king’s eyes.

274
00:14:42,316 --> 00:14:43,517
Killua: That proves it.

275
00:14:43,584 --> 00:14:46,353
I don’t know why,
but, for some reason,

276
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:49,256
this girl is
extremely important to the king,

277
00:14:49,323 --> 00:14:52,593
so, for gon and
for the sake of our mission,

278
00:14:52,659 --> 00:14:55,128
I can’t let
the enemy have her.

279
00:14:56,230 --> 00:14:57,765
Komugi: The person chasing us

280
00:14:57,831 --> 00:15:00,067
sounded a lot
like one of the people

281
00:15:00,133 --> 00:15:02,402
who was talking
with dear leader before.

282
00:15:02,469 --> 00:15:06,573
Does that mean the king
is dear leader?

283
00:15:07,674 --> 00:15:09,709
Then who is this,

284
00:15:09,776 --> 00:15:12,612
and who are
all the people he was with?

285
00:15:12,679 --> 00:15:15,415
Shaiapouf: Your twisted
sense of justice is pointless.

286
00:15:15,482 --> 00:15:18,018
You know it will
never benefit the people.

287
00:15:18,085 --> 00:15:19,219
( Komugi murmurs )

288
00:15:19,286 --> 00:15:20,721
Shaiapouf: First,

289
00:15:20,787 --> 00:15:22,956
i’ll put the girl
under my spell.

290
00:15:23,023 --> 00:15:26,193
Then i’ll use magic words
to make her suspicious.

291
00:15:27,394 --> 00:15:29,129
Stop right where you are!

292
00:15:29,196 --> 00:15:32,099
The king and I seek
an open dialogue with you!

293
00:15:32,166 --> 00:15:34,435
Now release the girl,
or face the consequences!

294
00:15:34,501 --> 00:15:37,604
Killua: Bastard.
That’s just a bunch of baloney.

295
00:15:37,671 --> 00:15:39,439
What is he up to?

296
00:15:39,506 --> 00:15:41,441
- Komugi: Let me go.
- ( Killua gasps )

297
00:15:41,508 --> 00:15:43,977
Komugi: Please put me down.
I beg you!

298
00:15:44,044 --> 00:15:45,379
Just let me go! You feel weird!

299
00:15:45,445 --> 00:15:47,380
Killua: Hey! What the hell
are you doing back there?!

300
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:49,249
Komugi: You’re all staticky,
and I don’t like it!

301
00:15:49,316 --> 00:15:51,285
Killua: What are you
talking about, you idiot?!

302
00:15:51,351 --> 00:15:52,752
I’m trying to save you,
damn it!

303
00:15:52,819 --> 00:15:54,421
Komugi: That’s a lie! ( Grunts )

304
00:15:54,488 --> 00:15:56,223
Killua: Oh, you think so, huh?

305
00:15:56,290 --> 00:15:58,759
You trust that insect
more than you trust me?

306
00:15:58,826 --> 00:16:02,096
Komugi: Insect? What insect?!
What are you talking about?!

307
00:16:02,162 --> 00:16:03,530
( Killua groans ) I forgot.

308
00:16:03,597 --> 00:16:05,499
- Komugi: Let go! Please!
- Killua: She can’t see.

309
00:16:05,566 --> 00:16:07,234
That’s gonna make it
pretty hard to explain.

310
00:16:07,301 --> 00:16:08,602
- Komugi: Just let me go!
- ( Killua gasps )

311
00:16:08,669 --> 00:16:10,704
( Komugi yells )

312
00:16:10,771 --> 00:16:12,373
- ( Heads thump )
- ( Groans )

313
00:16:12,439 --> 00:16:13,974
♪

314
00:16:14,041 --> 00:16:16,443
Shaiapouf: Damn it. Almost.

315
00:16:16,510 --> 00:16:18,445
( Laughs )

316
00:16:18,512 --> 00:16:21,215
It didn’t take long
for the poison to kick in.

317
00:16:21,281 --> 00:16:23,550
If the woman you’re
carrying chooses to resist,

318
00:16:23,617 --> 00:16:26,320
your speed is bound to suffer.

319
00:16:26,386 --> 00:16:28,655
♪

320
00:16:28,722 --> 00:16:31,024
Killua: What’s going on?

321
00:16:31,091 --> 00:16:32,526
He wasn’t aiming for me,

322
00:16:32,593 --> 00:16:35,262
which has to mean
he was aiming for the woman.

323
00:16:36,363 --> 00:16:38,265
He wanted to kill her.

324
00:16:42,669 --> 00:16:45,138
Shaiapouf: If she escapes,
that’s fine.

325
00:16:45,205 --> 00:16:47,107
If she distracts him
with her resistance,

326
00:16:47,174 --> 00:16:51,145
allowing me to kill her,
that’s all the better.

327
00:16:51,211 --> 00:16:53,180
Oh, miss komugi!

328
00:16:53,247 --> 00:16:56,217
The enemies see you
as a valuable hostage!

329
00:16:56,283 --> 00:17:00,087
They will not kill you,
so go on! Keep struggling!

330
00:17:00,153 --> 00:17:02,656
Keep fighting back
against your captors!

331
00:17:02,723 --> 00:17:05,159
I will save you soon!

332
00:17:05,225 --> 00:17:06,660
( Gasps )

333
00:17:06,727 --> 00:17:08,662
♪

334
00:17:10,330 --> 00:17:12,232
( Gasps )

335
00:17:13,333 --> 00:17:15,268
Killua: She’s knocked out.

336
00:17:15,335 --> 00:17:19,306
All right, I won’t pretend
to know what your deal is,

337
00:17:19,373 --> 00:17:20,708
but what I do know

338
00:17:20,774 --> 00:17:23,644
is that you’re really
starting to piss me off.

339
00:17:23,710 --> 00:17:26,046
( Electricity crackling )

340
00:17:32,019 --> 00:17:34,054
You step inside this circle...

341
00:17:35,155 --> 00:17:37,491
I’ll kill you.

342
00:17:37,558 --> 00:17:39,660
( Shaiapouf growls )

343
00:17:42,362 --> 00:17:44,264
♪

344
00:17:49,703 --> 00:17:51,972
Killua: It’s true
you might be a segment,

345
00:17:52,039 --> 00:17:53,274
but you were still formed

346
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:55,108
from the original’s cells,
weren’t you?

347
00:17:55,175 --> 00:17:58,712
I only have to burn them,
and they’ll die.

348
00:17:58,779 --> 00:18:01,215
Shaiapouf: Electricity.

349
00:18:02,316 --> 00:18:03,284
Killua: Come on.

350
00:18:03,350 --> 00:18:05,652
I’ll torch you piece by piece.

351
00:18:05,719 --> 00:18:07,254
( Shaiapouf groans )

352
00:18:07,321 --> 00:18:09,657
Meruem: Are you having trouble?

353
00:18:09,723 --> 00:18:11,225
( Shaiapouf gasps )

354
00:18:12,392 --> 00:18:14,461
Meruem: I can feel
your impatience.

355
00:18:14,528 --> 00:18:16,563
I shall lend you a hand.

356
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:19,533
Shaiapouf: There’s no need
to concern yourself.

357
00:18:19,600 --> 00:18:21,435
Your priority should be

358
00:18:21,502 --> 00:18:24,372
regaining your memory,
lord meruem.

359
00:18:24,438 --> 00:18:28,642
I’ll take them just as soon
as my body has returned.

360
00:18:31,245 --> 00:18:34,582
Lord meruem, feast your eyes
on the scene before you.

361
00:18:34,648 --> 00:18:36,450
♪

362
00:18:36,517 --> 00:18:38,986
Humans as far as we can see.

363
00:18:39,052 --> 00:18:41,187
Does this refresh your memory?

364
00:18:41,255 --> 00:18:43,190
They are here for you.

365
00:18:43,257 --> 00:18:46,694
Each one of them
belongs to you!

366
00:18:46,760 --> 00:18:49,696
Meruem: They belong to me?

367
00:18:49,763 --> 00:18:51,064
Shaiapouf: You will rule

368
00:18:51,131 --> 00:18:53,567
over these ignorant,
inferior creatures

369
00:18:53,634 --> 00:18:56,604
and stand proudly
atop the food chain!

370
00:18:56,670 --> 00:19:00,507
The entire world will shine
beneath your glorious light.

371
00:19:00,574 --> 00:19:03,010
This is your divine destiny!

372
00:19:05,479 --> 00:19:07,414
♪

373
00:19:14,655 --> 00:19:16,690
Meruem: Something isn’t right.

374
00:19:16,757 --> 00:19:18,125
Shaiapouf: Huh?

375
00:19:19,226 --> 00:19:21,428
Meruem: Something...

376
00:19:21,495 --> 00:19:25,165
Is missing, something important,

377
00:19:25,232 --> 00:19:27,468
something that isn’t this.

378
00:19:27,534 --> 00:19:29,069
( Shaiapouf gasps )

379
00:19:29,136 --> 00:19:32,006
What are you saying, sire?
You must be mistaken.

380
00:19:32,072 --> 00:19:35,542
Nothing could be more important
than ruling over all life forms.

381
00:19:36,710 --> 00:19:38,545
Meruem: Maybe you’re right.

382
00:19:40,080 --> 00:19:43,183
Perhaps the explosion
has left me confused.

383
00:19:43,250 --> 00:19:44,551
However...

384
00:19:48,288 --> 00:19:50,457
The pain won’t cease.

385
00:19:52,359 --> 00:19:55,996
Tell me, why is
the palace in shambles?

386
00:19:56,063 --> 00:19:59,300
Menthuthuyoupi: It was
destroyed during the battle.

387
00:19:59,366 --> 00:20:04,371
It broke out not very long after
you had left the palace, sire.

388
00:20:04,438 --> 00:20:08,409
Meruem: Now then, where do I
spend most of my time?

389
00:20:08,475 --> 00:20:12,179
Shaiapouf: The problem is,
sire, it’s been destroyed.

390
00:20:16,149 --> 00:20:18,618
Meruem: I suppose
I should see what’s left.

391
00:20:18,685 --> 00:20:20,086
Shaiapouf: Of course.

392
00:20:20,153 --> 00:20:21,321
It’s possible
you’ll find something

393
00:20:21,388 --> 00:20:23,156
to help jog
your memory down there.

394
00:20:23,223 --> 00:20:24,424
One can hope.

395
00:20:24,491 --> 00:20:27,027
( Gasping )

396
00:20:28,195 --> 00:20:30,431
This is bad.

397
00:20:30,497 --> 00:20:32,165
That could be it,

398
00:20:32,232 --> 00:20:34,601
the gungi board and pieces.

399
00:20:34,668 --> 00:20:36,336
( Killua gasps )

400
00:20:36,403 --> 00:20:40,240
Shaiapouf: If he sees them,
they’ll trigger his memory.

401
00:20:40,307 --> 00:20:43,610
I must dispose of them,
and quickly!

402
00:20:48,315 --> 00:20:50,350
Killua: He just gave up?

403
00:20:51,718 --> 00:20:53,653
( Wind blowing )

404
00:21:06,767 --> 00:21:08,302
Gon: Over there.

405
00:21:11,371 --> 00:21:13,139
♪

406
00:21:13,207 --> 00:21:14,475
Let’s go.

407
00:21:24,218 --> 00:21:26,153
( Singing in Japanese )

